  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nSay you are using the [`envString`](https://book.getfoundry.sh/cheatcodes/env-string?highlight=envString#envstring) cheatcode like this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nvm.createSelectFork(vm.envString(\"ETH_RPC_URL\"));\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe trouble is that if you have a global environment variable  `ETH_RPC_URL` (which is useful for `cast`) and also a local variable defined in an `.env` file, Forge will pick that global variable up instead of the local rpc URL defined in the `.env` file.\r\n\r\nMy feature request is to change this behavior to work in the opposite way - Forge should first look in the local `.env` file for any environment variables.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
